title: Oswego East’s offense too much for Plainfield Central football
text:
Oswego East’s offense too much for Plainfield Central football Published: Saturday, Oct. 10, 2015 12:37 a.m. CDT By KEVIN RYAN - Shaw Media Correspondent 
PLAINFIELD – Coming into their Week 7 matchup against Southwest Prairie foe Plainfield Central, Oswego East knew it was a must-win game in order to stay in the playoff hunt. Related Links Lockport football gets big stop to win game 
And the Wolves took care of business, beating the host Wildcats, 48-21, to keep their playoff hopes alive. 
Junior quarterback Jackson Piatek (18 for 27 for 273 yards) led the charge for the Wolves as East scored on four straight offensive possessions to put up 28 unanswered points in the first half. 
East (4-3, 2-3) continued its dominance in the second half as Devin Riley (6 carries for 85 yards) scored on runs from 11 and 65 yards, while also grabbing a 9-yard touchdown pass. 
“For us it’s win or go home,” East coach Tyson LeBlanc said. “We have to get to 6-3 overall because we won’t have enough playoff points at 5-4.”
